        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 5 at 12:57PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 1257 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
northwestern Custer State Park, or 5 miles south of Hill City, moving
east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Custer, Mount Rushmore National Memorial, Center Lake, Stockade Lake,
Custer State Park, Mount Coolidge, Legion Lake, State Game Lodge,
Black Elk Peak, Black Hills Playhouse, Sylvan Lake, and Blue Bell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
